FFF>(8/9/02 12:21:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> I agree with Baldrik, Complete Heal is the best spell in the game.<br>
<br>
Like Baps said, adding complete heal allowed an evolution past buff-zerg kunark type encounters.  These encounters are basically &quot;kill it fast before it kills you&quot; while velious encounters are controlled and precise.<br>
<br>
I love complete heal, I even made a cleric cause I thought it was cool (not just powerful, but fun).  It introduces a level of skill and precision into high end encounters that was not there before.  I tend to believe that most people who dislike it would simply prefer to mass zerg everything because they lack the skills to use it.<br>
<br>
Aamedor seems to dislike it because it prevents him from getting upgrades, but I don't really agree with this view either.  Cleric get constant upgrades, every expansion.  Every time more hp gear is introduced for tanks, clerics effectively get a better heal, since cheal scales up with the increased tank hp.  Clerics now essentially have up to an 8k heal (if you're healing Furor) whereas pre kunark they maybe had a 3k heal.  Their heals have gotten better every expansion, even if it is the same spell<br>
<br>
As wizards gain levels, their nukes get bigger.  As tanks gain levels, their ac/hp increase.  Rogue/monk/ranger/etc dps increases with level.  Mages get better pets.  etc etc.  Clerics get better heals as they level.  Some people just see that they are casting the same spell, but that spell gets a lot better as they level up.  So wizard upgrades are very direct, cleric upgrades involve the upgrading of the melees they heal, but an upgrade is still an upgrade.<br>
<br>
Griping about cheal getting stronger as clerics level makes no sense to me, all classes get stronger as they level.  Spell ratios get more efficient.  It is after all the reason we level.  I think it's sorta cool that verant made clerics power increases slightly different, in that their power increases through the melees that they heal, much like the damage they do is indirect, it's also through the melees they heal.<br>
<br>
The bottom line for me is that I like how the game evolved due to complete heal, without it, it would just be a massive zergfest that would fail to hold my interest and that would require very little healing skill.<br>
<br>
Oh and BTW Rsisa, I don't think you're right about LoS and AL not using cheals.  It's my understanding that while they do not use chains like most guilds do, they do indeed use cheals, they just use them differently.<br>
<br>
Ammelen, 60 Sorceror<br>
Ezelar, 60 Phantasmist<br>
