I am not sure where you got the idea I want the class variation to disappear. Honestly I want it to get far more apparent. I want a wizard such as yourself to be a wet piece of tissue paper when a mob decides to start beating on you compared to a plate wearing class such as myself. I want rogues to get far more into their true RP role where they are required for stealth and secret attacks and they are not the damage kings of EQ. I want monks to be what they were supposed to be, low AC armor warriors of their body, the weapons they are getting are stupid and the armor they get has rediculous amounts of AC, they are virtually warriors that can feign death and dish sick damage atm, they also tank better then every class but a defensive warrior. Rangers should be kings with the bow (and they are), they should be decent at best with hand held weapons (they are way too good with them atm). Bleh I gotta go, I could talk about every class but if anything this game has the classes all far to similar IMO. The only reason a CH chain is necessary is because warriors and the other plate classes cannot tank like they should be able to relative to the other classes and the encounters are usually single mob encounters instead of truely difficult wars between a huge amount of PC's and NPC's. In a huge battle with huge amounts of level 50 or so mobs and afew higher level mobs with maybe one major mob the classes would be able to fit into their true varied roles alot more, enchanters could mez and charm things, rogues could sneak around stabbing things, wizards could stand back and nuke various mobs while trying not to get hit, clerics would be healing various people with different spells as the differnt classes would tank very different and have very different hitpoint levels, monks could just run around and kung fu stuff with their bare hands and feet, SK's and palladins could run around taking things on toe to toe tanking as they should be able to, Warriors could attempt to piss off as many critters as possible and basically wade right into the heart of the battle, ect...... Very different roles for the classes in a very different kind of fight. Right now in EQ there are 3 classes<br>
<br>
1) Damage dealers<br>
<br>
2) Tanks<br>
<br>
3) Healers<br>
<br>
Pretty much thats it. Classes that dont fit into one of those 3 areas are screwed, they are basically buff bitches, mana bitches, or expendable as a whole. By making the fights more of a war like I mentioned and altering their skills and abilities as needs to happen all the classes would be useful, as it stands right now the big 3 classes are pretty much all that matter in a fight. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/ubackster.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Backster</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Contributing Member</span><br>  Posts: 248<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 3:48:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> You missed number 4 - crowd control - which is the reason that the game doesn't happen the way you foresee.  You don't fight 6 mobs at once in EQ, you fight one, then you fight the next...maybe it's mez that's broken, not CHeal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/umeiren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meiren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Senior Member</span><br>  Posts: 580<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/9/02 3:59:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3124.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 10k hp tanks</span><hr size=1> If you are going to attack mez, you certainly have to attack FD too.<br>
